                    '4' => 'Thorough alarm assessment: analyses the alarm pattern critically — while the sequential detector activation matches the condensation pattern, three additional factors change the risk profile: (1) steward\'s independent report of electrical smell at a specific cabin location, (2) warm door indicating heat source behind it, (3) visible haze at door base distinct from overhead condensation. Recognises that these combined indicators are inconsistent with HVAC condensation and consistent with a cabin fire (possibly electrical — overloaded socket, charging device, cabin electrical fault). Treats as real fire. Immediately escalates to fire emergency procedures.',
