ide > confirm) that takes approximately 20 seconds. The VLCC is sounding five short and rapid blasts on the whistle. Simultaneously, a cross-channel ferry on passage from Dover to Calais is detected at 4 NM on the port bow making 22 knots, creating a three-vessel close-quarters situation. Of the 4,200 passengers, the majority are in cabins sleeping, approximately 400 remain in bars and entertainment venues. You have been called to the bridge by the OOW. Time from your arrival on the bridge to potential collision with the VLCC is approximately 4 minutes.',
